<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Fang1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Fang,</orth> subst., the pointed tooth, tusk: <cit><quote>--s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 663" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 663</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 3, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.353" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 353</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.7.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 7, 58</bibl>. Figuratively: <cit><quote>the icy f. and churlish chiding of the winter's wind,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 1, 6</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>by the very --s of malice I swear,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.196" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 196</bibl></cit> (O. Edd. <emph>phangs).</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>